Date:  0/12/2001
Source:  Elements
Author:
Vol / Page:  13 : 4
Edition:
Quote:  The 'Judas' goat is fitted with a collar that has an antenna attached. It is then lowered into the forest by helicopter and because goats are social animals the Judas goat will find other goats. Later, the hunters' [sic] return by helicopter to the area and, using radio equipment, locate the Judas goat by picking up the signal from its antenna. The helicopter drops a hunter and dog on the ground to track the goats and shoot them.
